-- UAE lender NBAD Q1 net profit flat, beats estimates
-- By David French
-- Mon Apr 28, 2014 06:42AM EDT
-- None



DUBAI, April 28 (Reuters) - National Bank of Abu Dhabi <NBAD.AD>, the United Arab Emirates' largest lender by market value, reported flat growth in first-quarter net profit, beating analysts' forecasts.

The bank posted net profit of 1.41 billion dirhams ($383.9 million) in the first three months of 2014, the same figure as the corresponding quarter last year.